ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I will definitely recommend the course. However, the course is enroll-limited, so if you want to be enrolled, make sure you can appear in class one and get the permission asap.
Take it, if you have never taken a course in philosophy. Its challenging yet enlightening.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I've never have any foundation in philosophy before taking this class. The course systematically introduced many schools in the area of philosophy of mind. I was able to write argument to discuss on some topics of philosophy question, so it is really helpful for me to get into this area. In addition, it was really interesting.
Deepen my knowledge of artificial intelligence by illustrating the connections of human brain and robots. Help me look into the problems and well express myself clearly and logically.
